ple_job_board_company_logo',''),(3154,519,'editor_applicant','The ideal candidate for this Senior Sourcing Manager role will bring a wealth of experience in materials management, specifically with knowledge of metal and plastic fabrication at the manufacturing level. You will have a proven track record in managing level 2 sub-assemblies, power, interconnect, backplanes etc., and level 3 system design and integration. Your strong leadership skills will enable you to influence others and drive your team towards achieving operational excellence. Your excellent interpersonal skills will allow you to adapt your communication style to suit different individuals and situations. Your innovative approach to cost reduction through process optimisation will be highly valued.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Proven experience in materials management with working knowledge of metal and plastic fabrication at the manufacturing level</li>\r\n 	<li>Experience in level 2 sub-assemblies, power , interconnect, backplanes etc., and level 3 system design and integration</li>\r\n 	<li>Strong leadership skills with ability to influence others</li>\r\n 	<li>Excellent interpersonal skills with ability to adapt communication style accordingly</li>\r\n 	<li>Ability to identify creative ways to reduce cost by streamlining processes and systems</li>\r\n 	<li>Expertise in assigned commodities with full competency in all aspects of supply chain management</li>\r\n</ul>'),(3155,519,'editor_offer','For the right <strong>Renewable Energy - Vice President, Procurement - California </strong>there is:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Base salary of $300k+ - dependent on experience.</li>\r\n 	<li>Annual bonus 45%+</li>\r\n 	<li>LTIP - 50% of base</li>\r\n 	<li>Very competitive benefits package.</li>\r\n 	<li>Being part of a fantastic and well respected leadership team in the industry.</li>\r\n 	<li>Being in the room and having a seat at the table for decision making, working closely with CEO &amp; COO</li>\r\n 	<li>Open to being locat